s. The triatomines T. vitticeps and Panstrongylus geniculatus were found to be infected by trypanosomes via microscopy. According to molecular characterization, T. vitticeps specimens were infected with T. c. cruzi TcI, TcII, TcIII/V, and TcIV, T. c. marinkellei and T. dionisii. We observed high trypanosome diversity in a small and fragmented region of the Atlantic Forest. This diversity was primarily maintained by bats and T. vitticeps. Our findings show that the host specificity of the Trypanosoma genus should be thoroughly reviewed. In addition, our data show that CD cases can occur without an enzootic cycle near residential areas.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Dario, Maria Augusta", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lisboa, Cristiane Varella", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Costa, Luciana M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Moratelli, Ricardo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Nascimento, Monique Pereira", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Costa, Leonora Pires", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leite, Yuri Luiz Reis", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Llewellyn, Martin S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Xavier, Samanta Cristina Das Chagas", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Roque, Andr\u00e9 Luiz Rodrigues", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jansen, Ana Maria", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Solari, Aldo", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/566b8bb171486d01a0bb838376187acf", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/4c8d617576fa52700bbcc87d6edb37af6995c53be2f88d94e00d3e71d27270a7", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/BXGAFYV7", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/BXGAFYV7", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/c